<!--
  THEMIS TH02-A7 — floating-base MJCF.

  Body tree, inertials, and joint axes adopted verbatim from themis_rl
  (src/themis_training/themis/xmls/themis_29dof.xml). That file is the
  hand-authored canonical sim model — its L/R inertials mirror cleanly,
  joint axes are explicit (axis="0 1 0" for pitch, etc.), and gravity-
  settling drift is ~8× smaller than what MuJoCo's URDF importer gave us.

  Additions on top of themis_rl's body tree:
    * `<compiler meshdir="../meshes/">`         — point at our vendored mesh dir
    * mesh refs stripped of `_rot`/`_rot2`/`_ball` suffixes — canonical meshes
      vendored from THEMIS-Simulation-Model. NOTE: those canonical meshes are
      not pre-rotated, so visual orientation of limb geometry will be off
      relative to body frames. Dynamics + collisions are correct; only the
      visual mesh rendering is slightly twisted. To fix visuals, source the
      `_rot`/`_rot2`/`_ball` mesh set from themis_rl or apply per-mesh
      `refquat` in the asset block.
    * `<option>` block (timestep, gravity, warmstart)
    * `<actuator>` block with implicit-PD (general, biastype=affine)
      gains from themis_constants.py
    * Per-joint `<jointpos>` and `<jointvel>` sensors for ObkJointEncoders
    * `<keyframe name="ic">` with themis_rl/sim2real/config.py DEFAULT_JOINT_POS
      — i.e. POLICY frame, NOT HW frame.

  ⚠ Frame convention: this MJCF is in POLICY frame (themis_rl's training MJCF).
  AOS hardware expects HW frame. The two differ by the JOINT_SIGN/JOINT_OFFSET
  transform in themis_rl/sim2real/joint_mapping.py (q_hw = sign*(q_pol-offset)).
  For hardware deployment the on-robot bridge (themis_obk_server.py) needs to
  apply this transform on commands going to AOS and on state coming back.
  Currently this is a TODO — sim works correctly; hardware path needs the
  transform wired before it will produce a clean stand.
-->
<mujoco model="themis-29dof">

  <compiler angle="radian" meshdir="../meshes/" eulerseq="xyz" />

  <option timestep="0.001" gravity="0 0 -9.81">
    <flag warmstart="enable"/>
  </option>

