       with themis_rl's body frames. Canonical (un-rotated) meshes are preserved in
       ../meshes_canonical_backup/ in case anyone needs to regenerate.
       This bypasses MuJoCo's mesh-data post-processing (which silently mangles refquat
       and geom-quat values via principal-axis alignment) — see git history for the
       investigation that led here. -->
